<% content_for :title do %>Workspace setup | <%= installation_brand_name %> User Guide<% end %>
<% content_for :meta_description do %>
  Step-by-step instructions to create a <%= installation_brand_name %> workspace, sign in, and invite your team.
<% end %>

<h1>Workspace setup</h1>
<p class="lead">
  A workspace is your company’s shared environment in <%= installation_brand_name %>.
  Each workspace has its own inboxes, agents, and customer conversations.
</p>

<h2>Before you start</h2>
<ul>
  <li>A business email address you can access</li>
  <li>Admin access if you are joining an existing workspace (your admin sends an invite)</li>
  <li>Registration enabled on this installation (contact the operator if signup is closed)</li>
</ul>

<h2>1. Create a workspace</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="/app/auth/signup">Sign up</a>.</li>
  <li>Enter your name, work email, password, and company or workspace name.</li>
  <li>Confirm your email if confirmation is required.</li>
  <li>Sign in at <a href="/app/login">Sign in</a>.</li>
</ol>
<p>
  The first user in a new workspace is typically an <strong>administrator</strong> with permission to add inboxes,
  invite agents, and change settings.
</p>

<h2>2. Complete first-time setup</h2>
<p>After your first login, you may be guided through:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Naming your support team or company profile</li>
  <li>Creating your first inbox (email, website chat, or messaging)</li>
  <li>Adding agents to that inbox</li>
</ul>
<p>
  If you skip onboarding, go to <strong>Settings → Inboxes → Add inbox</strong> when you are ready.
</p>

<h2>3. Invite your team</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Go to <strong>Settings → Agents</strong>.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Add agent</strong> and enter each teammate’s email.</li>
  <li>Choose their role (administrator or agent).</li>
  <li>Assign them to the correct inboxes under <strong>Settings → Inboxes → [inbox] → Collaborators</strong>.</li>
</ol>

<h2>4. Sign in with Google (optional)</h2>
<p>
  If enabled, you can use <strong>Sign in with Google</strong> on the login page.
  This authenticates your user account only. Connecting a Gmail inbox for support email is a separate step under
  <a href="<%= guide_page_path('channels') %>">Connect channels</a>.
</p>

<h2>You’re done when</h2>
<ul>
  <li>You can sign in and see your workspace dashboard</li>
  <li>At least one inbox exists (or you know which channel you will connect next)</li>
  <li>Teammates who need access have been invited</li>
</ul>

<div class="cta-box">
  <p><strong>Next step:</strong> <a href="<%= guide_page_path('channels') %>">Connect your first channel</a>
  or read <a href="<%= guide_page_path('admin') %>">For admins</a>.</p>
</div>
